news.title: Bhubaneswar: Homebuyers of Dhauli Heights face further delay in allotment
news.para: Responding to queries raised by different MLAs in the assembly on the status of allotment of houses in Dhauli Heights, the minister recently stated that Odisha Police Housing and Welfare Corporation (OPHWC) completed the construction and handed over the project to OCHC

news.title: Pune: Residents, developers urge approval of development plan for merged villages
news.para: The planned development in the 11 villages merged with PMC seven years ago is on a slow track. On the other hand, unauthorised constructions and encroachments are rampant.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Bidding deadline for QUAD project in Technopark extended to December 18
news.para: The project aims to select a private co-developer to build and operate an 8 lakh sqft IT building at Pallipuram. Initially, the deadline for the revised request for proposal (RFP) was March 12, which was later extended to May 7 and subsequently to June 18 due to a lack of bidder participation.

news.title: Supreme Court stays BMC's demolition of illegal construction in Vakola
news.para: Justices Vikram Nath and Prasanna Varale of SC took up the hearing on Thursday 3.55pm and noted that in a contempt petition, "some order was passed yesterday...apparently, permitting BMC to demolish the first floor of the building in respect to which the status quo order is operating".

news.title: Bengaluru civic body collects Rs 4,284 crore in property tax till November 2024
news.para: The civic body received Rs 521.3 crore tax through offline payments and a staggering Rs 3,762.8 crore online.

news.title: Info Edge files fraud complaint against 4B Networks' founder
news.para: Consumer internet group Info Edge files an FIR against Rahul Yadav and others, citing fraud involving 4B Networks' funds. Info Edge had invested Rs 295 crore in the startup.

news.title: Indian corporates monetise non-core real estate assets worth Rs 14,200 crore in two years
news.para: By capitalising on favourable market conditions, several organisations across industries have strategically monetised these non-core assets across the country.

news.title: Delhi development body issues 83 conveyance deeds in PM-UDAY camps
news.para: Thousands of people visited the camp on Pradhan Mantri-Unauthorised Colonies in Delhi Awas Adhikar Yojana (PM-UDAY) scheme organised by the DDA on its first day on Saturday to sort out issues related to the scheme.

news.title: Allahabad HC quashes Noida authority’s rejection of building plan application
news.para: Kapil Misra and another villager — the petitioners — sought the Authority's permission to construct residential buildings on a Sector 45 plot that they received through an exchange agreement over a decade ago.

news.title: NGT directs BramhaCorp to pay Rs 3.11 crore for environmental norms violations in Pune project
news.para: The project — spread over an area of 17,433.10 sq m — involves five buildings, four of which are completed, with a total of 249 flats (194 completed) and an overall built-up area of 41,500 sq m.

news.title: Holcim to sell Lafarge Africa stake to Huaxin Cement in $1 billion deal
news.para: The deal aligns with Holcim's strategy to streamline its portfolio and focus on high-growth regions, including the coming spin-off of its North American business, which remains on track for a U.S. listing in the first half of 2025.

news.title: Dakshina Kannada district cancels 1,537 fake construction workers’ ID cards
news.para: The Mangaluru division of the labour department issued directions to return invalid construction workers' ID cards or face legal action.

news.title: Rs 10 lakh incentive for societies that clear 80% property tax: Badshapur MLA
news.para: ​Speaking at a meeting in Sector 108, which saw participation of 32 RWAs of sectors off the Dwarka Expressway, the minister said his first goal was to eliminate corruption as residents raised civic issues such as poor road conditions, inadequate drainage, lack of streetlights, road dust, and encroachment.

news.title: Dallas Technology Centre to lease its premise to TCS in Visakhapatnam
news.para: DTC has submitted requests for an occupancy certificate, permission to sub-lease the premises to TCS, and allocation of an additional 1,600 sqm at the original rate of Rs 6,720 per sqm.

news.title: Odisha RERA lists builders who failed to pay fines totalling Rs 6 crore
news.para: As per ORERA records, over Rs 6.89 crore in fines was imposed on 60 realtors for the violations, out of which only Rs 23 lakh has been realised so far. Only three promoters paid the penalty amount.

news.title: China's Kaisa to hold shareholder meeting to discuss restructuring in December
news.para: The developer has been working to restructure its debt since defaulting on $12 billion in offshore bonds in late 2021.

news.title: Coastal areas in Ernakulam to see CRZ relaxation with release of KCZMP
news.para: As per the KCZMP, 10 local bodies have become urban panchayats, which enables people living here to construct and reconstruct their homes, sheds, etc.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body proposes separate municipal corporation for Dharwad
news.para: The long-standing request for an independent corporation received consent from the HDMC general body, with councillors across party lines urging officials to submit the proposal.
